rules: Rule1: If the freelancer possesses programming skill, then the freelancer holds a programming certification.
Rule2: Either the freelancer possesses programming skill or the freelancer has internet access.
Rule3: Under the condition that the freelancer has references, the freelancer is available for a project.
Rule4: Whenever the client is an enterprise member, the client is a premium member.
Rule5: If the freelancer has a verified payment method, then the freelancer is available for a project.
Rule6: Supposing the freelancer has completed a milestone in project1, there is not a payment hold on the freelancer.
Rule7: Either the freelancer has completed a milestone in project1 or the freelancer has submitted deliverables for project1.
Rule8: Either the client has approved the freelancer for project1 or the freelancer has been auto-approved for project1.
Rule9: Under the condition that the freelancer has been auto-approved for project1, whenever the freelancer has submitted deliverables for project1, there is not a payment hold on the freelancer.
Rule10: Whenever project1 has been successful for the freelancer, the freelancer has received a bonus for project1.
Rule11: Either project1 has been successful for the freelancer or project1 has been extended for the freelancer.

Rule12: Provided that project1 has been extended for the freelancer, if the client has approved the freelancer for project1, then, under the condition that the freelancer has submitted deliverables for project1, there is not a payment hold on the freelancer.

Rule13: Supposing the freelancer has received a bonus for project1, then, in the event that the client has approved the freelancer for project1, whenever the freelancer has submitted deliverables for project1, it is not the case that there is a payment hold on the freelancer.
Rule14: If the client has an urgent project, then the freelancer is available for a project.
Rule15: Under the condition that the client has a high-priority project, the freelancer is available for a project.
Rule16: If the client has posted a project, then the client has an active project.
Rule17: Under the condition that the client has an active project, the client has a project in progress.
Rule18: If the client has a project that is completing, then the client has an urgent project or the client has a high-priority project.
Rule19: Either the freelancer has completed a web development course or the freelancer has completed a mobile development course.

Rule20: Under the condition that the client has extended a deadline, if it is not the case that whenever the client has a project in progress, the client has a project that is completing, then the client does not have a delayed project.
Rule21: Provided that the freelancer has completed a mobile development course, if the freelancer possesses programming skill, then the freelancer does not hold a programming certification.

Rule22: If the freelancer is available for a project, then, whenever it is not the case that if the freelancer does not have internet access, then the freelancer owns a laptop, the freelancer is capable of working remotely.
Rule23: Supposing the freelancer maintains a portfolio, the freelancer is available for a project.
Rule24: Either the freelancer maintains a portfolio or the freelancer has references.
Rule25: If it is not the case that whenever the client has a project in progress, the client has a project that is completing, then the client has a delayed project.

Rule26: Under the condition that it is not the case that if the freelancer has completed a web development course, then, whenever the freelancer possesses programming skill, the freelancer does not hold a programming certification, the freelancer has passed a coding test exam.

Rule27: Provided that it is not the case that if it is not the case that if the freelancer does not have internet access, then the freelancer does not have a desktop computer, then the freelancer has office space, the client is an enterprise member.

Rule28: If it is not the case that if it is not the case that if the freelancer does not have internet access, then the freelancer does not have a desktop computer, then the freelancer has office space, then it is not the case that the client is a premium member.
Rule29: If the freelancer does not have a verified payment method, then there is a payment hold on the freelancer.
Rule30: Under the condition that the freelancer does not have internet access, the freelancer has a desktop computer.
Rule31: Provided that the freelancer does not have internet access, the freelancer does not own a laptop.
facts: Fact1: The client has posted a project.
Fact2: The client has extended a deadline.
Fact3: The freelancer does not have office space.
Fact4: The freelancer has not passed a coding test exam.
Fact5: The freelancer is not capable of working remotely.
